                <head>150. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On March 14, the Operations Coordinating Board approved a Progress Report on
                        <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5612/1. (Department of State, S/P–<gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files: Lot 62 D 1, <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                        >NSC</gloss> 5612 Series) <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5612/1 is
                    printed as <ref target="#d119">Document 119</ref>.</p>
                <p>At the <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> meeting on May 2, the Council,
                    according to <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Action No. 1711, “noted and
                    discussed” the Progress Report. (Department of State, S/S–<gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files (Miscellaneous) Files: Lot 66 D 95) The
                        <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> did not discuss the substance of the
                    Progress Report. (Memorandum of discussion by <persName corresp="#p_GSE1"
                        >Gleason</persName>, May 2; Eisenhower Library, Whitman File, <gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Records)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
